    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span>\n<p>Raj likes competitve programming very much and he was the problem setter of the coding contest in his college. He always liked to give a storyline to the questions he prepared. This time he had a very good question but he couldn't think of any storyline for that question. So he directly gave the question as:<br/>You are given an array of size n. All the elements of the array are from 0 to n-1 (inclusive). There are two different types of operations defined on the array.<br />\n<br /></br/></p>\n<ul>\n<li><b>1 l r x :</b> modify <b>a<sub>i</sub> = (a<sub>i</sub>+x) mod n</b> for all <b>l \u2264 i \u2264 r</b></li>\n<li><b>2 l r x :</b> print the number of indices i such that <b>a<sub>i</sub> = x </b> for all <b>l \u2264 i \u2264 r</b></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Now you are given a lot of queries of type 1 and type 2. Print the answer to each query of the second type.</p>\n<h3>Input Description</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The first line contain <b>n</b> and <b>q</b>, number of elements in the array and total number of queries to perform.</li>\n<li>Next line contains <b>n</b> values, elements of array A (initially).</li>\n<li>Next <b>q</b> lines contain queries of type 1 or type 2</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Output Description</h3>\n<p>For every query of second type, print the required answer.</p>\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<li><b>1</b> \u2264 <b>n,q</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>5</sup></b>, <b>0</b> \u2264 <b>A<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>n-1</b></li>\n<li><b>0</b> \u2264 <b>l</b> \u2264 <b>n-1</b>, <b>l</b> \u2264 <b>r</b> \u2264 <b>n-1</b>, <b>0</b> \u2264 <b>x</b> \u2264 <b>n-1</b></li>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n4 4\n0 1 1 2\n2 0 2 1\n1 0 1 1\n2 0 2 1\n2 0 3 3\n<h3>Output</h3>\n2\n2\n0\n</pre>",
